about:
Company Description by Thomasnet
Custom manufacturer of forged metal component parts for OEM's including impression die forgings, drop forgings, press forgings, closed die forgings, open die forgings, upset forgings & hammer forgings. Industrial blacksmithing & toolsmithing services are also available. Capable of CAD & CAM designing, EDM (electrical discharge machining), induction heating & rapid infrared heating. Precision tooling from composite welded construction is available. Forged materials include alloy steel, stainless steel, aluminum alloys, brass, copper, silicone iron, core iron, titanium & nickel based alloys. Internal machining such as punching, drilling, bending, coining, tapping, threading, polishing & plating are also available. Applications include heavy hinges, safe hinges, specialty lifting devices, component parts for hoist rings, electromechanical relay components & relay cores. Industries served are aircraft, construction, natural gas & banks. JIT delivery is available.

details: Manufacturer of flat top, plastic modular conveyor chains & belting used in many conveyor types including side flexing conveyors, inclined conveyors, accumulation rollers, & bucket elevators. Also providing conveyor chains in special materials such as steel, stainless steel, chemical resistant, antistatic, & flame retardant. USDA, FDA, DPI approved for food contact. Types of conveyor chains & belts include plastic slat top chains, steel slat top chains, special chains, snap-on chains, & flexible conveyor chains. Belts & chains come in several variants like straight running, side flexing, with or without tabs, magnet chains, beveled, tabbed, with rubber inserts, safety chains that prevent fingers & clothes from getting caught between the links, ribbed, flexible in several directions, clean hygiene, 18% & 22% openings for applications requiring drainage or airflow. Features & options include high strengths suitable for applications running at high speed, patented tab systems which require no tools for installation, non-vibrating, low noise level, light weight, low backline pressure, minimized product damage, wide range of standard acetals for optimal design flexibility, considerable tensile strength for medium to heavy-duty applications, tight transfer applications, low contact surface area, stable product transfer, cleanability, impact resistance, tensile strength & belt surfaces, & abrasion resistance. Industries served include: beverage, brewery, wine, soft drink, food, packaging, containers, dairies, crates, large items, automotive, bakery, bottling, corrugated, fruit & vegetables, meat, beef, pork, poultry, postal, seafood, snack food, & tire.

about:
Company Description by Thomasnet
Distributor of industrial pipes & supplies. Products include pipes, fittings & flanges, valves & automation products, structural metal & industrial supplies. Types of pipes include black galvanized pipes, stainless steel pipes, PVC pipes, CPVC pipes, seamless pipes, copper pipes & sanitary pipes. Industrial supplies such as conveyors, ladders, meters, regulators, saws, filters, gauges, strainers, rigid tools, fittings, flanges, valves, structural metal, pipe cutters, steel sinks, sealants & lubricants are available. Types of valves include ball valves, gate valves, globe valves, butterfly valves, check valves & solenoid valves. Structural metal products such as rods, flat bars, angles, sheets & square tubing are available. Types of fittings include elbows, tees, reducers, unions, bushings, solid square head plugs, bolts, nuts, cored square head plugs, counter sunk plugs, couplings, crosses, nipples, NPT ends & steel hose menders.
Company Description by Industrial Pipe & Supply Co., Inc.
Industrial Pipe and Supply Co., Inc. was founded in 1976 as a small family business serving the Gainesville, Georgia area with emphasis on the poultry industry.

Today, our service area covers the entire southeastern United States and a variety of industries. We have experienced tremendous growth in the past twenty years, and expect the growth trend to continue for the next twenty years.

As we look to the future, we are even more committed to fulfilling the needs of our customers by providing the quality service and superior products upon which our company was founded.

details: Manufacturer of flat top, plastic modular conveyor chains & belting used in many conveyor types including side flexing conveyors, inclined conveyors, accumulation rollers, & bucket elevators. about:
Company Description by Thomasnet
Manufacturer of cleaning products and chemicals such as degreasers, disinfectants, detergents, sanitizers, neutralizers, hand soap, deodorants, removers, bleaches and lubricants. Various types of cleaners include glass, dairy, floor, coffee pot, boat, metal, toilet bowl, pipeline, rug, sink, wall and wood. Private label and contract packaging services are offered. Accessories such as distribution trays, dispensers, spray bottles, buckets, mixing hose, pumps, pack openers and cleaning kits are also provided. Serves the food plant, janitorial, automotive, institutional, dairy, household and farm sanitation industries.
Company Description by Stearns Packaging Corp.
Stearns Packaging Corporation is a full-line compounder of liquid and powder cleaning products for the food plant, janitorial, institutional, dairy and household sanitation markets. Our packaging sizes include single portion pack sizes, quarts, half gallons, gallons, 5 gallon pails, and 55 gallon drums for liquids and a variety of sizes for powders too. Our specialty is portion control packaging of liquid and powder concentrates for a variety of end-users. We feature water soluble packaging for powders.

We are EPA, Safer Choice recognized manufacturer. Green Seal certified GS-37 products. EPA registered manufacturer of disinfectants and sanitizers under FIFRA. Producer of non-food compounds registered under the NSF "white book" program.

Private branding is available in all sizes, providing you a centrally located single source manufacturer that can expand your offering to include portion pack packaging under your private brand.
